Description. Female . body length 17.3 mm , fore wing length 16.5 mm (
Fig. 1
).

Head. Antennae incomplete, probably missing apical segment, with 101 segments remaining; third antennal segment 1.5 × fourth; width of face 1.4 × length of face and clypeus combined; malar space 0.9 × as long as mandible width; mandible width as long as hypoclypeal depression; distance between tentorial pits 1.3 × distance between pits and eyes (
Fig. 3
); second segment of maxillary palp widened apically, with long setae (
Fig. 5
); in dorsal view, length of eye 1.3 × as long as temple; in lateral view, width of eye 1.14 × as long as temple; ocelli small, POL:OD:OOL= 7 : 7 : 20 ; distance between front and hind ocelli 0.2 × as long as OOL (
Fig. 2
); face with long sparse setae; clypeus with a transverse carina; frons slightly depressed laterally, smooth; vertex and temple smooth, sparsely setose.

Mesosoma. Length of mesosoma 1.7 × as long as high; notauli absent; mesoscutum flat posteriorly; scutellar sulcus narrow, smooth; mesopleuron convex, smooth; metapleuron sparsely punctate, setose; propodeal spiracle subelliptical, 2.3 × as long as wide; propodeum slightly depressed medially, sparsely setose medially but more densely setose laterally (
Fig. 6
)

Wings. Fore wing: pterostigma 3.8 × as long as wide; r: 2 -SR: 3 -SR:SR 1 = 9 : 21 : 51 : 78 ; vein r arising just anterior of middle of pterostigma; vein cu-a perpendicular, slightly postfurcal (
Fig. 11
); second submarginal 2.7 × as long as its apical width. Hind wing: vein M+CU: 1 -M: 1 r-m:SC+R 1 = 18 : 80 : 32 : 21 ; vein 2 -SC+R horizontal (
Fig. 10
).

Legs. Length of hind femur:tibia:basitarsus:tarsus = 60 : 101 : 31 ; length of hind femur, tibia and basitarsus 3.15 , 10.1 and 5.16 × as long as their maximum width respectively; inner hind tibial spur 0.4 × as long as hind basitarsus; apex of hind tibia with long differentiated setae ventrally (
Fig. 13
).

Metasoma. First tergite 1.4 × as long as apical width, with median united carina and lateral crenulated grooves (
Fig. 7
); medial length of second tergite 1.2 × than third; second and third sutures wide, crenulate; second tergite largely striate; third and fourth tergites with dense divergent striae; fifth tergite smooth (
Fig. 8
); ovipositor sheath with long setae (
Fig. 12
); ovipositor deeply depressed and formed into four arch-like sections (
Fig. 9
).

Colour. Scapus and antennae black; palpi yellow; head yellow, except frons medially, vertex, temple and stemmaticum black (
Fig. 2
). Middle and lateral lobes of mesoscutum black; mesosternum black. Fore and middle legs yellow; hind leg black entirely. Fore wing vein yellow two third basally, black one third apically (
Fig. 11
); pterostigma yellow entirely; basal two third of hind wing yellow (
Fig. 10
), apical one third black. Metasomal tergites black, sternites white to ivory; ovipositor sheath black; ovipositor yellow, brownish yellow in arch-like sections (
Fig. 9
).

The new species appears to be close to
Z. aswada
from Indonesia (Sumatra) in having the base of the hind wing evenly setose, with only a small glabrous area close to vein cu-a (
Fig. 10
), and the setae of the ovipositor sheath long (
Fig. 12
). It differs principally in colouration: frons medially, stemmaticum and vertex black (
Fig. 2
); head (excluding frons, stemmaticum and vertex) yellow; middle and lateral lobes of mesoscutum and mesosternum black; fore and middle legs yellow; hind leg black entirely; metasomal tergites black, sternites white to ivory; ovipositor sheath black; ovipositor yellow, brownish yellow in arch-like sections (
Fig. 9
).

Zaglyptogastra vietnamica
sp. n. differs from
Z. vitalisi
from Laos , in having the fourth metasomal tergite striate, and the fifth tergite smooth (both tergites are rugose in
vitalisi
); setae on ovipositor sheath long (short in
vitalisi
); propodeum sparsely setose antero-medially (densely setose in
vitalisi
).
