sp. n. differs from
Z. aswada El-Heneidy & Quicke, 2007
, from Indonesia , in having a shorter pterostigma, 3.8 × longer than wide ( 4.2 × in
aswada
); base of hind wing with a small glabrous area close to vein cu-a (larger and distal from vein cu-a in
aswada
); ovipositor sheath hairs long (short in
aswada
